description:
Locations: secretx-pkcs11/src/lib.rs:173-187 (EcParams), 271-284 (KeyType), 335-339 (Value/get), 424-428 (zeroize Value), 544-548 (PublicKeyInfo). Six near-identical loops that scan a Vec<Attribute> looking for one variant.

Suggested rewrite: a small helper that collapses each loop to one line:

fn extract_attribute<T, F: FnOnce(Attribute) -> Option<T>>(
    attrs: Vec<Attribute>,
    extractor: F,
) -> Option<T> {
    attrs.into_iter().find_map(extractor)
}

Or, cleaner, use a macro-free helper per attribute type:

fn first_value(attrs: Vec<Attribute>) -> Option<Vec<u8>> {
    attrs.into_iter().find_map(|a| match a {
        Attribute::Value(v) => Some(v),
        _ => None,
    })
}

Each callsite drops from 5 lines (loop + if-let + return + close) to 1-2 lines (find_map + ok_or). Removes a class of bug (forgetting to early-return inside the loop) and makes the surrounding structure read top-to-bottom.
